<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-07-28T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-07-28T00:00:00-05:00" n="1219" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1219">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">761.93/7–2845: Telegram</note>
                            <head>No. 1219<lb/><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_HMGPJ1" type="to"><hi rend="italic">Hurley</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#left"><hi rend="smallcaps">top secret</hi></seg>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Babelsberg</hi></placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-07-28">July 28,
                                    1945</date>.</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>Please deliver as soon as possible the following message to Doctor
                                    <persName corresp="#p_STV1">Soong</persName>: <quote rend="blockquote">
                                    <p>I understand you were to communicate with Marshal <persName corresp="#p_SGIV1">Stalin</persName> by 30th or 31st
                                        July. I think it important that before that date you
                                        communicate with him here through Moscow requesting
                                        opportunity to return to Moscow and continue discussions in
                                        hope of reaching agreement.</p>
                                </quote></p>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>